  "text": "A popular approach to this question is to correlate phenotypic and sequence evolution across the branches of a phylogenetic tree [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . This typically requires identifying groups of branches (e.g., subtrees) sharing a common molecular evolutionary process. Usually this branch-clustering step is performed a priori and reflects existing knowledge (or hypothesis) about the major factors affecting sequence evolution in the group of organisms under study.",
